\title{the principle of well-founded induction}
\date{2024-01-31}
\author{jonmsterling}
\contributor{marcelofiore}
\taxon{proposition}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{Let #{\prec\colon A\relto A} be a [well-founded relation](jms-00NL) and fix a subset #{S\subseteq A}. Then #{A\subseteq S} holds if and only if for each #{x\in A} such that #{\forall y\in A\punctdot y\prec x\implies y\in S}, we have #{x\in S}.}

\p{In other words, to show that every element of #{A} lies in #{S}, it is enough to show that for any element #{x\in A}, the elements below #{x} lie in #{S}.}